tners for Loyyal. Structure, negotiate and close key opportunities and partnerships. Have strong working knowledge of the Loyyal\u2019s Platform and services and be able to present the value of said solutions to the appropriate audiences. Responsible for attaining assigned booking targets in the form of sales quota. Generate leads and drive sales bookings for Loyyal products and services within designated territory and or accounts. Formulate the strategies, tactics and account plans, under the direction of management, necessary to develop the leads and relationships within assigned territory/accounts Travel to client sites, present sales materials and conduct product demonstrations to potential clients. Manage the effective and rapid movement of leads through sales process, including qualification of prospects; assessment of potential client needs; presentment of Loyyal solutions; and expeditious closing of business. Responsible for the daily maintenance of prompt and accurate sales pipeline forecasting. Regular reporting of task status CEO/revenue team. Requirements Extensive experience with a variety of deal structures including strategic partnerships, licensing and distribution. 5+ years hands-on experience in a global consultative sales role, preferably at an enterprise software vendor, ideally a loyalty management system. Strong organisational and process focused tendencies. Strong network of senior relationships at relevant companies. Ability and desire to manage a territory independently. A strong product focus and ability to effectively and quickly build relationships and establish trust, respect, and communication. Positive attitude and unsurpassed client relationship management skills. Demonstrated ability to handle multiple projects simultaneously and in a timely manner. Results-oriented. If this sounds like you please reach out with your resume to jobs@loyyal.com Loyyal is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We\u2019re committed to building a diverse and inclusive team. We do not discriminate against qualified employees or applicants because of race, color, religion, gender identity, sex, sexual preference, sexual identity, pregnancy, national origin, ancestry, citizenship, age, marital status, physical disability, mental disability, medical condition, military status, or any other characteristic protected by local law or ordinance. ", 
